## What this repo is
One Third Budget is a single-screen, mobile-first budgeting coach built with Next.js App Router. It helps users keep low-stress control over optional spending with calm plain-language prompts and local-only persistence.

## System map
- Layout and primitives: `app/layout.tsx`, `app/globals.css`, and `components/ui/*`.
- Page shell and feature orchestration: `app/page.tsx`.
- Money parsing/math core: `lib/types.ts`, `lib/money.ts`, `lib/money.test.ts`.
- Draft persistence: `lib/storage.ts`.
- Saved month persistence: `lib/monthLogs.ts`.
- Bucket behavior: `components/buckets/BucketCard.tsx`.
- Summary and chart visuals: `components/SummaryDonut.tsx`.
- Coach and flow: `components/NextMoveCoach.tsx`.
- Living build map and component contracts: `final_build/BUILD_MAP.txt` plus component specs in `final_build/`.

## Entrypoints and run commands
- How to run locally: `npm install` then `npm run dev`, open `http://localhost:3000`.
- How to build: `npm run build`.
- How to test: `npm test` (money utility tests are in `lib/money.test.ts`).
- How to lint/format/typecheck: `npm run lint` (Next.js type checks run during build).
- Environment notes: no backend, no env vars, localStorage only.

